From 380650273d0b7c5c251dce794b799b303a92f3eb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Saba Touheed Mujawar <sabatouheed.mujawar@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 10:18:31 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Kubelet Enable cgroup v1 support by default

Kubernetes v1.35 defaults FailCgroupV1 to true, causing kubeadm init
to fail at preflight with a fatal SystemVerification error on cgroup
v1 hosts.

Set FailCgroupV1 default to false and downgrade the preflight check
from error to warning, allowing the kubelet to start on cgroup v1
systems while still notifying users of the deprecation.

This is a short-term workaround until full migration to cgroup v2 is
completed, after which these changes should be removed.

Signed-off-by: Saba Touheed Mujawar <sabatouheed.mujawar@windriver.com>
---
 pkg/kubelet/apis/config/v1beta1/defaults.go    |  2 +-
 .../apis/config/v1beta1/defaults_test.go       | 18 +++++++++---------
 .../validators/cgroup_validator_linux.go       |  2 +-
 3 files changed, 11 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

